sts: 313<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/8/03 11:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=655.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback from our 1.62 Skald Report</span><hr size=1> Hybrids should get a buff to increase spell damage. Why do melee get to increase 100% of their damage output and casters get to increase 100% of their damage output but hybrids only get to increase 50-75% of their damage output (the melee portion)? That means that if a hybrid is balanced unbuffed it's not as balanced buffed. If it's balanced buffed it's not as balanced unbuffed. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnagrakk>Gnagrakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/03 12:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=655.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback from our 1.62 Skald Report</span><hr size=1> -----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This is common for many classes and not specific to the skald. With the recent block/parry changes, players should explore the options of making trade offs to raise parry if they want more in the area of melee defense. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The problem here is that there is no viable Skald spec with Parry over 25. With only 1.5 points and a spell line that simply can not be specced below 43, there isn't enough points left to get a meaningful defense *and* offense. And a high Parry rating serves no purpose on someone with a low weapon spec, as there simply is no point for said someone to go into melee range any more.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
Alternate templates are a good thing. We don't want there to be one single &quot;best&quot; template, so we'd look at this as a positive. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Except this isn't an alternate template. ALL Skald templates are based on the &quot;Minimum 43 BS for the last speed, weapon spec as high as possible, leftover into parry&quot; paradigm. This is just the most extreme variant of it. It, however, shows that more and more skalds consider the BS line to be of limited value except for the speed song, and Parry to be useless ( as it doesn't bring any tangible benefit unless specced higher than most Skalds can afford to).<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This is a change that affected all DAs. As far as the realm abilities, we'll be reviewing all the underperformers at some point in time, but have no plans to adjust the skald's specifically. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Disappointing. Very disappointing. And not only from a Skald's point of view. There are some very ugly imbalances in the whole Class RAs system.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This helps skald defense as well. While it makes it more difficult for everyone to attack targets with such defenses, it has no affect regarding skalds and &quot;softer&quot; targets. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Except, again, Skalds do not have any significant way to spec defensively. So the change widened the gulf between us and &quot;real&quot; melee classes, and nothing more.<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
Nice report. Feel free to keep pushing the defensive issue. But right now, we really want to proceed with caution when evaluating any changes to the classes defense. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------- <br>
<br>
By this, I understand that you feel that you have boosted (game wide) defense enough in relation to offense for now. However, the defense concerns of the Skald class predate the general changes made to the game to lengthen combat. And they haven't really been solved, we still have a short life span compared to similar classes. This would be acceptable if our offense still worked as it used to, but this is no longer the case. So the concerns remain.<br>
<br>
(Edited my original response)<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnagrakk>Gnagrakk</A> at: 7/9/03 1:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=benz@teamskald>Benz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/03 2:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=655.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback from our 1.62 Skald Report</span><hr size=1> Well my first 50 toon was a Skald, and after having played almost every other class (except animist) to some extent, I would have to say Skald's are among the most bland and boring.  Skalds have also suffered from little to no adjustments over the course of the last year or so and feel like an aged class.<br>
<br>
First of all, my Skald is incredibly 1 dimensional.  Why am I needed in any group??? Simple.. speed.  That is it, we are a one trick pony and once you get used to speed it is not fun and requires no skill to use.  Here is a summary of my experiences in PvE, RvR, and Duels with a Skald.<br>
<br>
PvE<br>
You are basically there only to help the group arrive at their destination quickly and then run battle chant.  We can kind of pull aggro from healers by saving our shouts, but that is a bit of a lost art now that we are resisted so much.  Pulling is not a great option as our snare slow the enemy rediculously when it sticks, and we can normally not survive extended time with aggro.  Battle chant is still flawed, suffers from bugs, and helps only marginally.  You really can't tank, you can't control aggro, and most do not good damage.  Having aggro is normally a mana drain to the healers due to our lack of defense and hp.<br>
<br>
RvR<br>
You are there for one reason... speed.  Multiple Skald groups used to do good front loaded damage by /assisting and opening up with shouts, but they are resisted and do such little damage in RvR they are no where near impactful anymore.  Once in battle if you remember you can switch to battle chant, which helps the group if they are not out of the short range or they do not get any of the missing pulses bug.  This requires both end and pow btw.  Melee is mildly effective, I normally use 1 hander and shield since Hib PBT is so prevalant and the ONLY chance we have to stun (sword spec) is off the block style Frost cut chain.  Due to our low defense, low hp, and high profile normal driver role (most af the Skald) we are often first to die.  Our main effectiveness is to hang back, find a caster and try to run in/flank and take them down.  We can not guard or protect healers as with our lack of defense and low hp we are mearly a speed bump on the road to the healer.  Our mez is also incredibly short duration, on a long timer, a major mana (some end drain), and barely noticeable to party members.  Snare and mez are often resisted and even with these cc methods Skalds have little to no chance at escape due to the length of reactivating Run Song.<br>
<br>
Duels/1on1<br>
I often open with 2 quick dds and a snare.  I then try to stay out of melee range as long as possible trying to regain DD timer.  Once in combat we are normally at a major defensive disadvantage.  2 hander is blocked/misses very often and/or nulified by PBT and 1 hander lacks the 110% damage of 2 hander.  Damage output is decent when combined with damage add but due to fairly low (40-44) weapon specs, style choices are fairly limited and often result in polar rift or main anytime style spammage.  As you begin to lose the fight, Skalds will often try to mez and then run or heal up with FA.  Then reopen with DDs and return to melee.<br>
<br>
Overall, I think Skalds are semi-effective but a very limited a dated class that I have absolutely no fun playing.  Here are some suggestions.<br>
<br>
Defense:<br>
Since the defense was uped, Skalds have suffer immensely.  Now Mythic rebutts that Skalds were also helped.. however that actually is incorrect.  The defense issue was compounded and more negative to Skalds because they A: Have limited spec points to invest in parry.  B: Can only use small shield which does not block multiple targets.  C: Do not have shield spec.  D: Have limited evade skills.  Skalds parry benefited slightly yes (this may even be debatable), while enemy's Parry, Shield, Evade, Advanced Evade, Guard, Intercept, and Large Shield blocking were all improved.  Skalds need shield spec and medium shield.  When this is coupled with the low hp of the Skald and the high cost of IP, their lifespan is very short.<br>
<br>
Beneficial Song Besides Run:<br>
Lets face it, Skald damage add is dated, boring, bugged, and was left behind in the times patches ago.  Skalds need some other group support to help in both RvR and PvE.  Personally I think a celerity song would be ideal as one option.  I also feel Skald's should have been the class to receive end regen.<br>
<br>
Review of Battle Song Line<br>
Not only has there never been a reason to take BS to 50, but most are even going lower than the final shouts which used to be our bread and butter.  We need higher damage, shorter timer, and high level (Less resisted) shouts.<br>
<br>
RA<br>
Fury of the Gods is a joke.  This RA needs a complete revamp.  <br>
<br>
This is one person's experience, not just as a Skald but from a multiple class point of view.  I'm not crying that Skald's suck, because they don't.  However, I am saying they are very little fun to play, offer very little in support, and feel like an outdated class.  I would like to see my Skald be fun or interesting to play again, but I don't see that happening anytime soon.  Best of luck with all your efforts Roseanne.<br>
<br>
Blough - 50 Skald<br>
Benz - 50 SB<br>
Bennz - 50 Healer<br>
Dapper - 35 RM<br>
Puba - 45.5 Reaver<br>
Durham - 38 Cleric<br>
And many more.<br>
<br>
